# 🔍 Hash-Powered Spell Checker

A complete spell checker built **from scratch in Python** to learn core hashing concepts through a real project.

**No external libraries used.** Every data structure is hand-coded.

---

## 📚 Hashing Concepts Covered

| Concept | Where |
|---|---|
| Hash Functions (Polynomial Rolling) | `hash_table.py` → `_hash()` |
| Collision Resolution (Separate Chaining) | `hash_table.py` → `insert()` |
| Load Factor & Dynamic Rehashing | `hash_table.py` → `_rehash()` |
| Bloom Filters (probabilistic hashing) | `bloom_filter.py` |
| Multiple Hash Functions / Double Hashing | `bloom_filter.py` → `_hashes()` |
| FNV-1a & djb2 Hash Functions | `bloom_filter.py` |
| Hash Sets (for suggestion candidates) | `spell_checker.py` → `suggest()` |
| Two-stage lookup (Bloom + Hash Table) | `spell_checker.py` → `is_correct()` |

---

## 🗂 Project Structure

```
spell_checker_project/
├── hash_table.py      # Custom hash table with chaining + rehashing
├── bloom_filter.py    # Bloom filter with k hash functions
├── spell_checker.py   # Main engine combining both structures
├── main.py            # CLI interface with multiple modes
├── tests.py           # Full test suite (19 tests)
└── README.md
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
# Clone and run
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/hash-spell-checker
cd hash-spell-checker

# Interactive mode (check words one by one)
python main.py

# See all hashing concepts demonstrated live
python main.py --demo

# Check a paragraph of text
python main.py --text

# Check a file
python main.py --file myessay.txt

# See internal hash table stats
python main.py --stats

# Run all tests
python tests.py

# Load a custom dictionary (one word per line)
python main.py --words mydict.txt
```

---

## 🧠 Architecture

```
User Input
    │
    ▼
SpellChecker.is_correct(word)
    │
    ├─► Stage 1: BloomFilter.might_contain(word)
    │       └── Uses k=7 independent hash functions on bit array
    │           If NO → definitely misspelled (skip stage 2)
    │           If MAYBE → proceed to stage 2
    │
    └─► Stage 2: HashTable.search(word)
            └── Polynomial hash → bucket → walk chain
                Returns True/False (definitive answer)
```

---

## 🔬 Key Learning Points

### 1. Hash Function
```python
def _hash(self, key):
    PRIME = 31
    hash_value = 0
    for i, char in enumerate(key):
        hash_value += ord(char) * (PRIME ** i)
    return hash_value % self.capacity
```
Maps a string → integer index in O(n) time where n = word length.

### 2. Collision Resolution (Chaining)
When two words hash to the same bucket, they form a **linked list**:
```
bucket[42] → "apple" → "apex" → "apt" → None
```

### 3. Load Factor & Rehashing
```
Load Factor = words_stored / num_buckets
```
When load factor > 0.7 → double the bucket array and re-insert everything.

### 4. Bloom Filter
Uses 7 independent hash functions. Sets 7 bits on insert. Checks all 7 bits on lookup.
Memory: ~1.2 MB for 100,000 words vs ~5 MB for a plain hash table.

### 5. Spell Suggestions
Generates all edit-distance-1 candidates (~54n words), then checks each in O(1) using the hash table.

